Ekiti House of Assembly, on Thursday, paid glowing tribute to the late Evang. Adeola Alofe, a former Secretary to the State Government (SSG) and House of Representatives member in the Third Republic, for selfless service during his lifetime. The lawmakers eulogised the deceased during the Assembly’s special session, presided over by the Speaker, Mr Funminiyi Afuye in Ado-Ekiti. In their separate remarks,  Mr Abiodun Fawekun, Mrs Yemisi Ayokunle, Mr Akin Oso and Mr Olajide Adegoke described the late Alofe as “an epitome of selflessness and a loving father.” They said the fatherly advice of the late cleric and politician would be greatly missed, praying that the Almighty God grant him eternal rest. Responding on behalf of the family, Mr Ademola Alofe, the former SSG’s son, thanked the lawmakers for their kind words on his late father. The high point of the occasion included the reading of Alofe’s biography by the Deputy Majority Leader, Mr Tajudeen Akingbolu, and paying of last respect to the late politician led by the speaker. Alofe, an indigene of Ayetoro-Ekiti in Ido-Osi Local Government Area of the state, died on August  25, 2019, at the age of 86 and was SSG between 2003 and 2005.